OMG LOL if tinkering could make those, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> EVERY</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> gnome would be being paid by his/her guild to be able to.  Unfortunately the Bag of Tinkers was added way back when to be a money sink to eliminate plat from the economy.  Its was used to replace the Box of Abu'Kar that once dropped with fair frequency from Specters.<br>
<br>
LOL this isn't poking fun at ya, Ashr, just... OMG I haven't laughed so hard in a LONG time.  I once built a gnome enchanter JUST so he could tinker/jewelcraft, but tinkering was at that point, and for the most part still is fairly useless.  The best thing tinkers really make are rebreathers, and those mainly for warrior epics.<br>
<br>
I won't say there aren't some nifty toys and trinkets that they can make, in fact at one point the only way to find a compass for those too lazy to max sense heading was to get a tinker to do it, but now they are in most newbie zones for purchase.<br>
